               <head>Conrad de Brundelsheim, etc.; Germany, c. 1400</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <note>On the upper pastedown are contemporary notes on preaching, citing Augustine etc.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Hamilton_15-item1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1ra-238va; 238vb blank)</locus>
                     <author key="person_84969355">Conrad de Brundelsheim ('Soccus')</author>
                     <title key="work_1309">Sermones de tempore</title>
                     <!-- http://www.ub.uni-koeln.de/cdm/search?searchterm=is00589000&field=istc -->
                     <note>(pars hyemalis, with supplementary Lenten sermons)</note>
                     <incipit><cit>
                           <quote>Exsurge amortuis et illuminabit te christus</quote>
                           <bibl>Ephe. vº.</bibl>
                        </cit> Cogitanti michi quod dominum patrem peccatis meis grauiter offenderim</incipit>
                     <msItem>
                        <note>(fols. 1r-58r): Schneyer, I, 716–47, nos. 1–36.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 58r-59r)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Conuertimini ad me in toto corde vestro</quote>
                           <note>[gap left]</note> cor nostrum intra nos positum </incipit>
                        <explicit>gaudium tuum et tristicia eque conuertantur adipsum ihesum christum dominum nostrum</explicit>
                        <!-- similar incipit in Soccus sermones in Frankfurt (Main) MS. Barth. 119 f. 121 -->
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <note>(fols. 59–160v): Conrad de Brundelsheim, nos. 38–57, 61, 58–60, 62–86, [fol. 142v] 91–100.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 160va-162vb)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Ductus est Iesus in desertum</quote> ut supra. Dubitaret aliquis quomodo siue a quo spiritu ductus fuerit Iesus</incipit>
                        <explicit>sitis extinccionem. Quod nobis prestare dignetur Iesus Christus Marie Filius. Sequitur.</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 163ra-164rb)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Ecce nunc tempus acceptabile</quote> ubi supra. Nota quod est tempus de quo apocalipsis, Dedi illis tempus ut penitentiam agerent</incipit>
                        <explicit>benedicat nos benediccione gratie in presenti et benediccione glorie in futuro</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 164rb-164vb)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Ecce nunc tempus acceptabile.</quote>
                           <sic><unclear>Oriuntur</unclear></sic> quinque de causis illud tempus est tempus acceptabile</incipit>
                        <explicit>quia inuenitur quod perierat etc.</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 164vb-165ra)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Ecce nunc tempus acceptabile</quote> Nunc licet cuncta fecerit bona tempore suo tamen aliquid est bonum in uno tempore quid non valeat in alio</incipit>
                        <explicit>naute id est predicatores ad confessionem modo clama<supplied>n</supplied>t quod intrare debemus</explicit>
                        <note>Cf. Schneyer VIII, p. 574, no. 33.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 165ra-165va)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Ecce nunc tempus acceptabile</quote> Nota super illo verbo Gal. ijo, In faciem restiti ei</incipit>
                        <explicit>diuersitas intelligencie, quam nobis dominus</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 165va-169ra)</locus>
                        <author key="person_89204668"><supplied>Bertrandus de Turre</supplied></author>
                        <title key="work_6170"><supplied>Sermones de tempore et quadragesimales</supplied></title>
                        <note>(nos. 105–106; Schneyer I, pp. 513–14)</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 169ra-170rb)</locus>
                        <author key="person_100198644"><supplied>Jacobus de Voragine</supplied></author>
                        <title key="work_2334"><supplied>Sermones quadragesimales</supplied></title>
                        <note>(no. 206; Schneyer III, p. 239)</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 170rb-173ra)</locus>
                        <author key="person_89204668"><supplied>Bertrandus de Turre</supplied></author>
                        <title key="work_6170"><supplied>Sermones de tempore et quadragesimales</supplied></title>
                        <note>(nos. 107–108; Schneyer I, p. 514)</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 173ra-173vb)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Cum introisset ierusalimam comota est vniuersa ciuitas</quote> Istud evangelium legitur in dominica palmarum suprascriptum quando dominus cum magno honore susceptus est</incipit>
                        <explicit>qui implebitur dilectione fruicionis perfecte</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 173vb-174rb)</locus>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>In diebus illis dixit dominus ad moysem ascende ad me</quote>
                              <bibl>Exo xxiiijo</bibl>
                           </cit> In lectione immediate preexposita monuit sancta mater ecclesia populos christianos malam viam deserere</incipit>
                        <explicit>constituit terminos iuxta mandatum domini ad radios montis</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 174rb-vb)</locus>
                        <rubric>Feria vjta in quatuor temporibus ante reminiscere <note>[later hand]</note></rubric>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Anima que peccauerit ipsa morietur</quote>
                              <bibl>Ezek. viijo</bibl>
                           </cit> Ubi notandum quod illa scilicet mors nihil aliud est nisi peccatum</incipit>
                        <explicit>culpa originalis post baptismum</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 174vb-175rb)</locus>
                        <incipit>
                           <cit>
                              <quote>Postea inuenit eum iesus in templo dominus ei Ecce sanus factus es iam noli peccare ne deterius etc.</quote>
                              <bibl>Ioh vo</bibl>
                           </cit> Saluator noster in verbis istis tria facit. Primo commemorat impensum beneficium. Secundo proponit optimum consilium</incipit>
                        <explicit>Bene ergo dixit, Iam amplius noli peccare</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 175rb-176ra)</locus>
                        <rubric>Sabato <note>[later hand]</note></rubric>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Post dies vj assumpsit iesus petrum Jacobum et Johannem</quote>
                              <bibl>Mt xvijo</bibl>
                           </cit> Et duxit eos in montem Thabor excelsum ut <choice><sic>ora<gap reason="illegible"/></sic><reg>oraret</reg></choice> Luc. autem xiiijo dicitur Post dies octo signans eundem diem </incipit>
                        <explicit>Quia ignis illuminat et inflammat, quam illuminacionem nobis concedat</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <note>(fols. 176r-181r): Conrad de Brundelsheim, nos. 101–103.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 181rb-va)</locus>
                        <rubric>Dominica reminiscere epistola <note>[later hand]</note></rubric>
                        <incipit>
                           <cit>
                              <quote>Rogamus vos et obsecramus in domino iesu</quote>
                              <bibl>Thess. 4o</bibl>
                           </cit> Finis et conclusio huius epistole est de sanctificacione quia nullus potest videre gloriam dei nisi sit sanctus et sanctificatus</incipit>
                        <explicit>superbia vita. Expone sicud potes. Sequitur.</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 181va-b)</locus>
                        <author key="person_5320656"><supplied>Johannes de Castello</supplied></author>
                        <title key="work_6242"><supplied>Sermones de tempore</supplied></title>
                        <note>(no. 121; Schneyer, III, p. 383)</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 182ra-183rb)</locus>
                        <author key="person_100198644"><supplied>Jacobus de Voragine</supplied></author>
                        <title key="work_2334"><supplied>Sermones quadragesimales</supplied></title>
                        <note>(no. 216; Schneyer III, p. 239)</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fol. 183rb-vb)</locus>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Et apparuerunt illi Moyses et Helyas</quote>
                           </cit> Querit Ambrosius, Quomodo cognouerunt eos quos nunquam viderant</incipit>
                        <explicit>Petrus credebat cum petra cristo se habitaturum</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <note>(fols. 183v-187r): Conrad de Brundelsheim, nos. 104–105.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 187rb-18vb)</locus>
                        <rubric>Dominica oculi ewangelium <note>[later hand]</note></rubric>
                        <incipit><cit>
                              <quote>Beatus venter qui te portavit</quote>
                              <bibl>Luc. xjo</bibl>
                           </cit> Vbi nota quod vij sunt genera portantium aliquid a Christo</incipit>
                        <explicit>portate et glorificate dominum in corde et corpore</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <locus>(fols. 187vb-188va)</locus>
                        <incipit><quote>Loquente iesu ad turbas</quote> Nota <choice><sic>in uenitus</sic><reg>inuenimus</reg></choice> in sacra scriptura septem <unclear>miserabiles</unclear> locuciones. Prima est serpentis</incipit>
                        <explicit>patet quomodo expellitur de iure demon de peccatrice anima</explicit>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem>
                        <note>(fols. 188va-238v): Conrad de Brundelsheim, nos. 106–131.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <explicit>a domino maledicti ut in Deuteronymo Maledictus adeo omnis qui pendet in ligno</explicit>
                     <!-- https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=FdfJEuId3Y4C&lpg=PA558&ots=i5L7yvwHnG&dq=%22primo%20angeli%20habent%20gaudium%22&pg=PA194#v=onepage&q=%22primo%20angeli%20habent%20gaudium%22&f=false -->
                     <note>The sequence of material on fols. 160va-188va is closely paralleled in <bibl subtype="external" type="ms">Gotha, Forschungsbibliothek, Chart. A. 1928</bibl> fols. 180ra-217ra, in a collection of Lent sermons there attributed to Henricus de Frimaria.</note>
                     <note>Attributed to <persName cert="low" key="person_4472713" role="aut">Simon Cassia</persName> by early owners: fol. 249r 'pars yemalis sucus symonis'; fol. i recto, 'Iste liber intitulatur pars yemalis Sermonum Symonis de Cassia'; contents label, front cover.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 239r; 239v blank)</locus>
                     <incipit><quote>Mortuo non prohibeas graciam</quote> Ecci. 7o. Tanto graciosius est opus misercordie subuenientis. Et quia ne<supplied reason="omitted">m</supplied>o pauperior hiis qui in purgatorio detinentur </incipit>
                     <explicit defective="true">Unde sensus est Non exibunt</explicit>
                     <note>Schneyer VI, p. 431 (no. 42; the full incipit is 'Quanto major est necessitas indigentis, tanto...'); also in <bibl subtype="external" type="ms">Zwettl, Zisterzienserstift, Cod. 206</bibl>. Ends unfinished.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fols. 240ra-244vb)</locus>
                     <author key="person_24629057"><supplied>Johannes Andreae</supplied></author>
                     <title key="work_6241">De modo observandi interdictum</title>
                     <incipit>De modo obseruandi interdictum memoriale quoddam simplicibus colligendo</incipit>
                     <explicit defective="true">non diffiniendo sed propo</explicit>
                     <note>Ends imperfect (at f. 11r of ISTC ia00629000).</note>
                     <!-- https://app.digitale-sammlungen.de/bookshelf/bsb00044163/view?currentUrl=%2Fview%2Fbsb00044163%3Fview%3DImageView&manifest=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.digitale-sammlungen.de%2Fiiif%2Fpresentation%2Fv2%2Fbsb00044163%2Fmanifest&canvas=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.digitale-sammlungen.de%2Fiiif%2Fpresentation%2Fv2%2Fbsb00044163%2Fcanvas%2F15&view=ImageView -->
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fols. 245ra-246va; 246vb, 247r blank)</locus>
                     <title key="work_15091" type="desc">Treatise on the mass</title>
                     <incipit defective="true">in f<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>mis. Nam de miraculo veteris panis exodi</incipit>
                     <explicit>omnem suam dulcedinem infundit in epulum quod nobis prestare dignetur</explicit>
                     <note type="addition">Begins imperfect; contemporary addition (?).</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 247v; fol. 248r blank)</locus>
                     <rubric>De concubinariis constitucio In <orgName key="org_147193963">concilio Basiliensi</orgName> facta et est talis</rubric>
                     <incipit>Licet aduersus clericos publice concubinas tenentes multa a sanctis patribus </incipit>
                     <note type="addition">Added, fifteenth century; cf. Mansi, XXIX, 102–3, but the text here differs considerably.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 248v)</locus>
                     <rubric>In prohemio <unclear>applica</unclear></rubric>
                     <incipit>Has autem <sic>misticationes</sic> quis enarrabit? puteus namque altus est. Joh. iiij. Quis enim cognovit sensum domini, quoniam incomprebensibilia sunt iudicia eius</incipit>
                     <note type="addition">Added, fifteenth century; an extract from the prologue to <persName key="person_84976644" role="aut">Nicolaus Stoer</persName>, <title key="work_3337">Expositio officii missae</title>.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus>(fol. 249r, stub)</locus>
